cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.CG, cs.DM. 

The paper deals with the problem of labeling nodes in trees, which is a fundamental problem in data structures (cs.DS). The labeling scheme has applications to XML trees (cs.DB) and partially ordered sets (cs.DM). The paper also mentions the use of the labeling scheme for answering ancestry queries, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper involves constructing small universal posets, which is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG).
